The initiative includes 100 different general and specialised ways of volunteering.

We Are Durban is one of the nonprofit organisations on the “Mandela 100” list who train skilled professionals to use their skills to empower “social dignity organisations.”

“We get professional people with their professional skill to volunteer their skill into the different non-profit organisations in Durban,” said Linda Morrison from We are Durban.

Craig Roodt from Container World is one of the corporates who are on a mission to make the vision of Durban being “a dream city” a reality.

“My challenge to corporates is to start an ubuntu revolution by collaborating and using organisations like the Denis Hurley Center and their partners to bring about social change.

As corporate citizens we have the ability to mobilise and we have the economic power to enable great organisations to do great things in our city.,”said Roodt















